                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4885/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Bolivian Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Bolivia</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform Your Excellency that
                    this legation has received cable advice that the election of the President and
                    Vice Presidents for the term beginning August 6, 1909, and ending August 6,
                    1913, took place on the 2d instant.</p>
                <p>The Hon. Eleodoro Villazon received a majority of the votes for President, the
                    Hon. Macario Pinilla for First Vice President, and the Hon. Juan M. Saracho for
                    Second Vice President.</p>
                <p>In bringing the foregoing to Your Excellency’s knowledge, I wish to add that
                    perfect quiet prevails throughout the Republic.</p>
                <p>With greatest respect, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">I. Calderon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
